MASSIVE UPDATE. Quality models can now be edited in the browser. Admin has control over two quality models - one that groups metrics/factoids by their source (vcs, cc, bts), and another that groups by quality attribute. Furthermore, each user can define their own quality model. A new user preference has been added to the profile page that allows users to switch between different quality models. I expect we will need to migrate the existing web app DB (to incorporate the new quality models) before pushing this to the server.
Added a 'vanilla' feature and product configuration - excludes all existing metric providers, to allow developers of metrics/managers to test their code with the bare minimum selected.
